org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.transformation.library.transformations

Class AbstractBootLoaderGen

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.transformation.library.transformations.AbstractBootLoaderGen
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IM2MTrafoCDP, IM2MTrafo

    public abstract class AbstractBootLoaderGen
extends Object
implements IM2MTrafoCDP
    The task of the boot-loader is twofold: create the instances of all implementations (non-recursive). - create Connections: what should be done? TODO: factor out common code (TemplateInstantiation mechanism & createConnections below) Split between C++ specific and C++ independent aspects

      • hasUnconnectedStartRoutine

        public static boolean hasUnconnectedStartRoutine(LazyCopier copier,
                                                 org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Class implementation,
                                                 org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Slot containerSlot)
        Check whether the passed implementation has an unconnected start port. This information is required, since only unconnected start ports are automatically called by the bootloader, in particular we want to avoid calling a start port of an executor (which is connected) and its container.

        containerSlot -
        Returns:

      • instantiateViaBootloader

        protected boolean instantiateViaBootloader(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.StructuralFeature structuralFeature)
        Normally, a composite instantiates its children. However, we want to enable the possibility to type a part in a composite with an abstract class and choose the concrete implementation in the moment of the deployment. In this case, the bootloader needs to perform the instantiation.
        Parameters:
        structuralFeature - a structural feature in a composition (typically an attribute)
        Returns:
        true, if the boot loader should instantiate the associated component.
